<HEADLINE>
NEW IMMIGRATION AGENCY OPENS SERVICE OFFICES THROUGHOUT COUNTRY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  2 (CNA) 01/02/07  19:44:22 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The upgraded National Immigration Agency under the Ministry of
the Interior formally began operations Tuesday, with the new
department simultaneously opening branch offices in all 25
counties and cities around the country.
</P>
<P>
The Taichung county office, located at No. 280, Chungshan Road in
Fengyuan City, provides services regarding the entry and exit of
Taiwanese; applications by citizens of China, Hong Kong and Macau
to enter, exit and stay in the country; foreign visitor
applications for resident permits; and helping immigrants adapt
to their new life on the island.
</P>
<P>
The office is open for service from 8 a.m. to 5: 30 p.m. from
Monday to Friday, with no midday break.
</P>
<P>
The National Immigration Agency is an enlargement of the Bureau
of Immigration, and incorporated with several other governmental
agencies in an effort to meet the increasing number of
applications by foreign spouses of locals and other foreign
visitors for residency permits in Taiwan.
</P>
